</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="11" pageNumber="72">
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1451,240,759]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">
<keyLead pageId="11" pageNumber="72">3 Pileal surface glabrous; spores subfusiform, with a conspicuous suprahilar depression; in North and Central America and Europe ............................................................................................................................................................................................................4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1451,240,759]" box="[136,1451,471,493]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,471,493]" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">
3 Pileal surface felty-tomentose; spores ovoid-ellipsoid, with an inconspicuous suprahilar depression; in 
<collectingCountry box="[1197,1287,471,493]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">East Asia</collectingCountry>
.......... 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuan Zhao et Zhu L. Yang" baseAuthorityName="W. F. Chiu, Mycologia" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[1357,1451,471,493]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletaceae" genus="Rubroboletus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="11" pageNumber="72" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sinicus">
<emphasis box="[1357,1451,471,493]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="72">R. sinicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="11" pageNumber="72">
